title: Fateh Ullah Khan wins NA-45
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) candidate Fateh Ullah Khan won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-45 D.I.Khan-II by securing 56,993 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Obaid ur Rehman Jamiat-e-ulema Islam Pakistan candidate, who bagged 48,343 votes.
Over-all votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 49.98 per cent.
